  '8beff72c-5a9e-430d-9cc6-799ea213cdc9',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Optimism EVM Architecture — Understanding Opcodes, Gas Model, and Data Storage$escape$,
  $escape$Optimism's EVM (Ethereum Virtual Machine) architecture relies on a stack-based execution model, utilizing opcodes to perform operations. The gas model determines the cost of each operation, with the goal of preventing denial-of-service attacks. Data is stored in three main areas: memory, storage, and calldata. Memory is used for temporary data, storage for persistent data, and calldata for function arguments. Optimism's EVM implementation, based on the Bedrock protocol, optimizes gas costs and execution efficiency. Understanding these components is crucial for building efficient and secure smart contracts on Optimism.$escape$,
  $escape$null$escape$,
  $escape$null$escape$,
